article.description: Papa Dia went 10-for-10, scoring 23 points to pace SMU to a 79-65 victory over Southern Mississippi on Saturday.
article.headline: Papa Dia leads way as SMU tops Southern Mississippi
article.linkText: Dia leads way as SMU tops Southern Mississippi
article.story: DALLAS -- Papa Dia went 10-for-10, scoring 23 points to pace SMU to a 79-65 victory over Southern Mississippi on Saturday. The Mustangs (11-8, 2/3 Conference USA) shot 69.8 percent (30 of 43) in the second-best shooting performance in school history. Robert Nyakundi scored 16 points, Collin Mangrum 15 and Rodney Clinkscales 12 for SMU, which broke a two-game losing streak and won for the ninth time in its last 11 home games. Angelo Johnson's 16 points led the Golden Eagles (14-5, 3-3), and Gary Flowers had 12. The Mustangs also made 12 of 18 3-pointers (66.7 percent), with Clinkscales hitting four and Mangrum and Nyakundi three each. Dia blocked four shots to pass 100 for his career at 102, and Jeremiah Samarrippas had a career-high nine assists. SMU led 59-52 with 6:09 left, then went on 9-0 run keyed by five points by Dia to seal the win.
